            "body": "I tried the PR, thank you for the quick response, and the empty list issue is resolved, but my usecase is not fully working, and I think I did not frame my issue completely right\n\nactually for my usecase to work, the re-query should happen not only when list is empty, but also for non-empty list with isIncomplete = true, at the moment the type re-query stops as soon as results comeback, like typing `[[foo`, will stop re-querying as soon as `[[f` when that returns a result, but not do further query on `oo`, while the completion plugins I mentioned will do that, I am not sure about the bigger context, maybe just re-query when `isIncomplete` is true, without the new flag and the checking popup?",
